{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83f297d9-0ce2-4ba4-be85-bfb6e799cb8a","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes and `createdump` isn't available, you have two main options:\n\n1. **Apple Crash Reports** — macOS automatically generates `.ips` crash reports in:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n   These contain the stack trace, exception type, and faulting address. Open them with Console.app or any text editor.\n\n2. **Core dumps** — These are disabled by default. To enable them:\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited\n   ```\n   Then reproduce the crash. The core file location varies by macOS version; check `/cores/` for files named `core.<pid>`.\n\n**Tip:** The `.ips` crash reports are usually sufficient for initial triage and are always generated without any prior setup.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2ffb4bcf-8351-4091-916a-3d98c218fa23","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a knowledge question, not a code task. I can answer directly.","outputTokens":257,"requestId":"7852:13DD23:4A5ACB:55AF86:69FA9D83"},"id":"2b54f219-d862-405e-9a54-f236075ab660","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:46:51.796Z","parentId":"f7c426e9-1824-4516-b78a-94ceaaf9c1bc"}
